      • fromBytes

        public static Ed25519PrivateKey fromBytes(byte[] keyBytes)
        Construct an Ed25519PrivateKey from a raw byte array.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the key bytes are of an incorrect length for a raw private key or private key + public key, or do not represent a DER encoded Ed25519 private key.

      • fromMnemonic

        public static Ed25519PrivateKey fromMnemonic(Mnemonic mnemonic,
                                             String passphrase)
        Recover a private key from a mnemonic phrase compatible with the iOS and Android mobile wallets.
        Parameters:
        mnemonic - the mnemonic phrase which should be a 24 byte list of words.
        passphrase - the passphrase used to protect the mnemonic (not used in the mobile wallets, use fromMnemonic(Mnemonic) instead.)
        Returns:
        the recovered key; use derive(int) to get a key for an account index (0 for default account)

      • fromMnemonic

        public static Ed25519PrivateKey fromMnemonic(Mnemonic mnemonic)
        Recover a private key from a mnemonic phrase compatible with the iOS and Android wallets.
        Parameters:
        mnemonic - the mnemonic phrase which should be a 24 byte list of words.
        Returns:
        the recovered key; use derive(int) to get a key for an account index (0 for default account)

      • supportsDerivation

        public boolean supportsDerivation()
        Check if this private key supports derivation. This is currently only the case if this private key was created from a mnemonic.

      • derive

        public Ed25519PrivateKey derive(int index)
        Given a wallet/account index, derive a child key compatible with the iOS and Android wallets. Use index 0 for the default account.
        Parameters:
        index - the wallet/account index of the account, 0 for the default account.
        Returns:
        the derived key
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this key does not support derivation.
        See Also:
        supportsDerivation()

      • fromPemFile

        public static Ed25519PrivateKey fromPemFile(File pemFile)
                                     throws IOException
        Parse a private key from a PEM encoded file using the default system charset to decode. This will read the first "PRIVATE KEY" section in the file as an Ed25519 private key.
        Throws:
        IOException - if one occurred while reading or if no "PRIVATE KEY" section was found

      • fromPemFile

        public static Ed25519PrivateKey fromPemFile(File pemFile,
                                            Charset charset)
                                     throws IOException
        Parse a private key from a PEM encoded file using the given Charset to decode. This will read the first "PRIVATE KEY" section in the file as an Ed25519 private key.
        Throws:
        IOException - if one occurred while reading or if no "PRIVATE KEY" section was found

      • fromPemFile

        public static Ed25519PrivateKey fromPemFile(Reader pemFile)
                                     throws IOException
        Parse a private key from a PEM encoded reader. This will read the first "PRIVATE KEY" section in the stream as an Ed25519 private key.
        Throws:
        IOException - if one occurred while reading or if no "PRIVATE KEY" section was found

      • fromString

        public static Ed25519PrivateKey fromString(String privateKeyString)
        Recover a private key from its text-encoded representation.
        Parameters:
        privateKeyString - the hex-encoded private key string
        Returns:
        the restored private key
        Throws:
        org.bouncycastle.util.encoders.DecoderException - if the hex string is invalid
        RuntimeException - if the decoded key was invalid

      • fromKeystore

        public static Ed25519PrivateKey fromKeystore(InputStream inputStream,
                                             String passphrase)
                                      throws IOException
        Recover a private key from an encrypted keystore file.
        Parameters:
        inputStream - the inputstream to read the keystore from
        passphrase - the passphrase used to encrypt the keystore
        Returns:
        the recovered key
        Throws:
        IOException - if any occurs while reading from the inputstream
        KeystoreParseException - if there is a problem with the keystore; most likely is if the passphrase is incorrect.

      • exportKeystore

        public void exportKeystore(OutputStream outputStream,
                           String passphrase)
                    throws IOException
        Export a keystore file to the given OutputStream encrypted with a given passphrase. You can recover this key later with fromKeystore(InputStream, String).
        Parameters:
        outputStream - the OutputStream to write the keystore to.
        passphrase - the passphrase to encrypt the keystore with.
        Throws:
        IOException - if any occurs while writing to the OutputStream
